9073771, 0.029634492, 0.042158023, -0.0024585945, 0.051902477, -0.0044626873, 0.025122434, -0.008835636, 0.006131579, 0.012203075, 0.03717172, 0.023324054, 0.009164526, -0.007912987, -0.01687769, 0.020284945, -0.016257474, 0.003008194, 0.043283645, -0.0015933079, 0.054533023, 0.030465143, -0.06544846, -0.024871036, 0.06464807, 0.0053946106, -0.046916686, -0.07589217, 0.0022421903, 0.012232316, -0.0063522332, 0.08519821, -0.049539812, -0.004262248, 0.0045169946, -0.0042247525, -9.730682E-4, -0.0324476, -0.0019930128, -0.01313359, 9.5155335E-4, -0.07912698, -0.0023595414, -0.08198003, -0.0595608, -0.018783892, 0.008796491, -0.0028409858, 0.022569906, -0.010551477, 0.01568949, -0.0114481, 0.04624244, 0.05269215, 0.050149444, 0.0026127556, 0.006875722, -0.032588508, 0.04665913, 0.0073546153, -0.0068796524, -0.011281952, 0.02766471, 0.05183434, 0.016330708, 0.04457631, -0.051861085, 0.02287226, 0.015256594, -0.037540603, 0.004103081, -0.028761968, -0.043873057], text:"tions, without amino acid changes but with altered protein expression, have also been identiﬁed as\nrisk factors for PD by GWAS [14–17]. Consistently, increasing studies have revealed elevated\nLRRK2 protein expression in some familial or sporadic cases of PD [14–16,18–21], indicating an\nimportant role of LRRK2 protein levels in PD pathogenesis. Notably, pathogenic mutations that\ndo not change LRRK2 enzymatic functions have been reported, suggesting that altered enzymatic\nfunctions are not the sole mechanism responsible for LRRK2-linked PD [6,22,23]. The notion that\nLRRK2 enzymatic functions are essential for maintaining normal LRRK2 protein levels has been\nemerging [24–27]. It is worth mentioning that the most promising LRRK2 kinase inhibitor,\nDNL151/ BIIB122, currently in clinical trials, has been reported to reduce total LRRK2 protein levels\nby about 50% in the cerebrospinal ﬂuid (CSF) at a moderate dose, and almost completely\nabolished LRRK2 protein levels in CSF in some patients at a higher dose [28]. Indeed, a recent\nstudy indicated that the levels of mutant LRRK2 were more predictive than kinase activity for its\npathogenic effect, suggesting that LRRK2 expression levels are crucial in the pathogenesis of\nLRRK2-associated PD [26]. Conversely, manipulation of LRRK2 levels has been shown to limit\nits toxicity [29–34]. All the evidence suggests that LRRK2 protein levels are important factors for\nLRRK2-associated PD, and destabilization of LRRK2 presents an attractive approach to limit its\ndetrimental effects.\nARM\nKinase          \nROC          \nLRR\nWD40  \nCOR\nANK\nG2019S\nR1441C/G/H/S\nI2020T\nY1699C\nP S1292\nS910\nS935\nP\nP\nN1437H\nTrends\nTrends in\nin Molecular\nMolecular Medicine\nMedicine\nFigure 1. LRRK2 domain structure, pathogenic mutations, and conﬁrmed phosphorylation sites. LRRK2 has seven\ndomains: ARM, armadillo; ANK, ankyrin; LRR, leucine-rich repeat; ROC, Ras of the complex; COR, C-terminal of ROC GTPase;", page:2}}, {_id:2515, properties:{chunk_index:2, id:"PIIS1471491424001898.pdf::p2::2::9f813802", embedding:[0.028419621, 0.095531605, -0.15974905, -0.028112637, 0.075090624, -0.054837715, -0.0040322775, 0.023997722, 0.01813068, -0.005533259, -0.01770778, 0.04958525, 0.09936586, 0.0022779244, 0.003961316, -0.050279357, -0.024671832, -0.0032832762, 0.01027256, 0.05582321, -0.07645761, 0.022762183, 0.017390208, -0.017868478, 0.07605207, 0.049010113, 0.00956848, -0.011852547, 0.017427811, 0.0010196788, 0.02798723, -0.03929015, -0.04270852, -0.025499646, -0.012301532, -0.03509604, 0.09933237, 0.021065848, 0.0056145736, 0.036017425, 0.045407273, 0.0510464, 0.027186314, -0.004743634, -0.0013880284, 0.030818693, -0.01148737, -0.005637925, 0.059598394, -0.053804774, 0.058125887, 0.03398892, 0.0031467539, -0.040894516, 0.10388593, 0.02604414, -0.003924819, 0.0375476, 0.032986376, -0.021922825, 0.080137014, 0.07620084, -0.06699192, 0.028838253, 0.06317601, -0.047154818, -0.0052796127, 0.041299157, -2.9688163E-4, -0.052464787, 0.06214041