2026805, 0.0048867287, -0.013008277, 0.01814908, -0.014148494, 0.050151505, 0.05591085, 0.004024904, 0.011870058, -0.061606206, 0.021984616, -0.006098798, 0.037705656, -0.03261741, 0.0062563536, -0.055489104, 0.008040965, -0.02382675, -0.0036680812, 0.011596769, -0.0043363697, -0.036015213, -0.012043448, -0.0180824, -0.016135897, 0.027686162, 0.009120813, -0.0032079876, -0.025512738, 0.041531414, 0.009370604, 0.02960733, 9.957016E-4, 0.039035276, 0.014211064, 0.0042819977, -0.013489901, 0.025126483, -5.6379254E-4, -0.0026722935, 0.010084107, 0.03328449, 0.00979416, 0.031688172, 0.0010425289, 0.03313022, -0.009791853, -0.052630067, -0.0033993854, 0.05336659, 0.037543293, -0.040573772, -0.058922417, -0.0077639353, 0.0037482565, -0.009482427, 0.061553646, -0.04010161, 0.011671061, -0.021576, -0.015443702, -0.0065339818, -0.02447072, 0.0051211007, -0.022945212, 0.022077024, -0.058175124, -0.006519713, -0.05335233, -0.05558477, -0.04367917, 0.025888568, -0.0030937511, 0.025063079, 0.008118552, 0.020755164, -0.005875633, 0.03403947, 0.054661445, 0.014788242, -0.0015619963, -8.636542E-4, 0.020273574, 0.01232885, -0.0055535375, 0.004549857, 0.010873353, 0.06044377, 0.06972665, 0.007917986, 0.0168309, -0.027212465, 7.9936313E-4, -0.009983005, -0.023273503, -0.014548913, -0.04561552, -0.045256093], text:"domains: ARM, armadillo; ANK, ankyrin; LRR, leucine-rich repeat; ROC, Ras of the complex; COR, C-terminal of ROC GTPase;\nkinase; and WD40. Eight pathogenic mutations in red segregated with the disease in large families. The autophosphorylation site\npSer1292 in green is the most widely studied and is used as a biomarker of LRRK2 kinase activity. The phosphorylation sites in the\nN-terminus, pSer910 and pSer935, are abundant and mediate LRRK2 binding to 14-3-3.\nTrends in Molecular Medicine\nTrends in Molecular Medicine, October 2024, Vol. 30, No. 10\n983\nGlossary\nEndolysosomal pathway: involves a\nseries of organelles, including\nendosomes, the trans-Golgi network\n(TGN), plasma membrane, and\nlysosomes, where various cargos are\ninternalized, transported, or recycled\nby a variety of endosomes, or are\ndegraded by lysosomes.\nFamilial PD: Parkinson's disease (PD)\nassociated with a speciﬁc gene mutation\nthat is inherited within a family.\nG-proteins activated by nucleotide-\ndependent dimerization (GADs): a\nmechanism of G-protein activation. In\nthis model, GTP binding enhances\ndimerization whereas GDP binding\nweakens it.\nGTPase-activating proteins (GAPs):\nproteins that stimulate the intrinsic\nGTPase hydrolysis activity of small\nGTPases and induce the inactive 'Off'\nGDP-bound state.\nGuanine nucleotide exchange\nfactors (GEFs): these load GTP and\ndissociate GDP from small GTPases\nand facilitate the interaction of small\nGTPases with downstream effectors\nand, in turn, activate downstream\nsignaling pathways.\nIdiopathic PD (iPD): PD of unknown\ncause; these comprise the majority of\nPD cases.\nPenetrance: the proportion of\nindividuals carrying a speciﬁc gene\nmutation who demonstrate the\nphenotype associated with a genetic\ndisease. For example, some LRRK2\nmutations have incomplete penetrance,\nmeaning that not all people carrying\nLRRK2 mutations will develop PD.", page:2}}, {_id:2519, properties:{chunk_index:0, id:"PIIS1471491424001898.pdf::p3::0::6d026b1c", embedding:[0.00590664, 0.07953718, -0.13327459, 0.02300382, 0.06502657, -0.05911552, 0.06530889, 0.05534433, 0.0021036589, -0.047957163, -0.054907724, 0.0687315, 0.10413905, -0.017419556, 0.045432784, -0.031239336, -0.015948718, 0.0010768453, 0.010015135, 0.09647318, -0.042647403, 0.013492835, 0.015274168, -0.02819766, 0.07277382, 0.05695894, 0.013975132, -0.032069832, -0.0067556254, 0.021805095, 0.027690025, -0.047436688, -0.026252566, -0.026285423, -0.029453421, -0.06043009, 0.10577591, 0.023582779, -0.007394079, -0.030368375, 0.04167751, 0.008531118, 0.008868926, -0.027803194, -0.02652809, -0.004769231, -0.008353823, -0.007323936, 0.044075247, -0.057170942, 0.