5220998, 0.013914977, -0.08634957, -0.051801626, -0.04461663, -0.02260133, -0.010538633, -0.021372996, 0.008233018, -0.020574551, 0.0089622, -0.014369169, 0.0081731295, -0.04235152, -0.015323971, 0.015023033, -0.0072883205, -0.025874479, 0.018716678, -0.061764415, 0.04862244, 0.054114714, 0.02544693, 0.031204872, -0.021975186, 0.05199889, -0.009084636, 0.0060513914, -0.029672407, -0.01586281, -0.018747753, 0.028657526, -0.043749478, -0.03128254, 0.024415806, 0.022263339, -0.030555584, -0.014880359, -0.020433147, 0.013888441, 0.0048870705, 0.023898877, 0.022991132, -0.048428528, 0.04606701, -0.009242944, 0.016269404, -0.019148674, 0.01394639, -0.02541469, -0.008160469, 0.014040848, 0.0019797669, -0.028192807, -0.029204844, -0.014324511, 0.042102914, -0.014504517, 0.053815205, 0.025961386, 0.036358085, -0.01435895, -0.007030386, -0.018862551, 0.02976167, 0.008075035, -0.023548901, -0.08109476, -0.0066192485, -0.012143471, 0.009072065, 0.086919755, -0.041700244, 0.004384645, 0.011838761, -0.03187455, -0.036994763, -0.041544005, -0.01500284, -0.027369749, 0.010292401, -0.042833194, -0.021332607, -0.036549207, -0.053343993, -0.05119592, -0.0015436336, 0.0028660942, 0.02760564, -0.019279769, 0.0076242043, -0.028015792, 0.04548333, 0.058055505, 0.0017342935, -0.0011203348, 0.028451253, -0.013530968, 0.036448553, 0.0249719, -0.0072978474, -0.03692028, 0.041281067, 0.0676418, -0.022706073, 0.04511286, -0.022666914, 0.026165968, -0.013203031, -0.020083157, -0.011558767, -0.035067692, -0.038373683], text:"also bind to the same site of LRRK2 as Rab29 [59]. Rab29/32/38 and Rab8/10 bind to the same site\nwhereas Rab12 binds to a different site of the LRRK2 ARM domain. These ﬁndings suggest that\ndifferent Rabs modulate LRRK2 activation by distinct mechanisms, and that Rab proteins can control\nLRRK2 by recruiting it to diverse membranes. Inhibition of Rab binding to LRRK2, or a decrease of\nthese Rab protein levels, may offer a novel avenue for LRRK2 inhibition. Furthermore, the PD-\nassociated mutation of the retromer complex component VPS35, D620N, enhances LRRK2-\nmediated Rab protein phosphorylation and induces LRRK2-mediated lysosomal association of\nRILPL1 and TMEM55B [60,61], suggesting another possible upstream pathway of LRRK2 activa-\ntion. Despite these advances, it remains to be determined how endogenous Rabs activate LRRK2\nin speciﬁc cell types, how exactly the different domains of LRRK2 are involved in membrane recruit-\nment, and how membrane-bound LRRK2 undergoes dimerization and activation.\nKey figure\nUpstream activation and downstream phosphorylation of LRRK2 and its\ncellular consequences\nTrends\nTrends in\nin Molecular\nMolecular Medicine\nMedicine\nFigure 2. Higher-order dimerization and membrane recruitment appear to be required for LRRK2 activation. LRRK2 kinase\nactivity is stimulated by Rab29, Rab12, Rab38, Rab32, and Rab8/10 through binding to the ARM domain of LRRK2. These\nRab proteins regulate LRRK2 by recruiting it to diverse membranes. Rab12 recruits LRRK2 to damaged lysosomes,\noverexpressed Rab29 recruits LRRK2 to the Golgi complex, whereas Rab38 recruits LRRK2 to the pericentriolar region.\nRab32, mutation of which has been recently linked to Parkinson's disease (PD), likely activates LRRK2 to stimulate Rab10\nphosphorylation. Rab8 and Rab10 as LRRK2 kinase substrates can also bind to the same site of LRRK2 as Rab29.\nRab29/32/38 and Rab8/10 bind to the same site whereas Rab12 binds to a different site of the LRRK2 ARM domain. A", page:4}}, {_id:2524, properties:{chunk_index:1, id:"PIIS1471491424001898.pdf::p4::1::bebb6be9", embedding:[-0.0018850304, 0.07340215, -0.13399583, -0.009563318, 0.084666364, -0.07821538, 0.020836547, 0.014858519, -0.0067139002, -0.03704759, -0.051262937, 0.026776051, 0.09066489, -0.017053168, 0.027222553, -0.06986502, 0.005382076, -0.043774802, 0.020443125, 0.09024049, -0.057952214, -0.013540852, 0.028015047, -0.033677265, 0.06299006, 0.056983728, 0.054355796, -0.03547897, -1.