etromer complex component VPS35 enhances LRRK2 kinase activity on Rab proteins. Loss of\nLRRK2:14-3-3 binding leads to destabilization of the LRRK2 inactive conformation and enhances kinase activity. In\naddition, the dimerization and capacity of LRRK2 to bind GTP are required for proper kinase activity. Endogenous LRRK2\nkinase phosphorylates a series of substrates, including endocytic proteins (EndoA, SYNJ1, auxilin/DNAJC6, AP2M1) and\na subset of Rab small GTPases, among others. These substrates perform distinct functions at different steps in the\nendolysosomal pathway as well as microtubule binding and cytoskeletal assembly including centrosomal function and\nciliogenesis. Abbreviations: Abbreviations: ANK, ankyrin; ARM, armadillo; COR, C-terminal of ROC GTPase; LRR, leucine-\nrich repeat; ROC, Ras of the complex. Figure created with BioRender.\nTrends in Molecular Medicine\nTrends in Molecular Medicine, October 2024, Vol. 30, No. 10\n985", page:4}}, {_id:2525, properties:{chunk_index:0, id:"PIIS1471491424001898.pdf::p5::0::8b3983da", embedding:[-0.007534944, 0.08211856, -0.1425646, -0.002778443, 0.10722409, -0.033797327, 0.021941865, 0.020817146, 0.016004566, -0.06295634, -0.053475156, 0.054483235, 0.08039914, -0.020307176, 0.04814391, -0.055023048, -0.025624394, -0.014903498, 0.0068533355, 0.08520734, -0.06258991, 0.010725456, 0.037541803, -0.02215992, 0.08299814, 0.051583942, 0.039649136, -0.010594792, -0.0057676625, 0.015231989, 0.028939458, -0.040662322, -0.027014434, -1.9285333E-4, -0.03931181, -0.05855914, 0.09187705, 0.02703027, 0.023810444, -0.008236648, -0.002246277, 0.030234754, 0.018191721, -0.03133256, 0.03508468, 0.005992039, -8.60291E-4, 0.006054869, 0.013445577, -0.070606366, 0.031819973, -0.011713366, -0.0075876685, -0.046296246, 0.1311739, 0.022393452, 0.0035868234, 0.045649085, 0.007877344, 0.018379979, 0.04707406, 0.055305745, -0.03955547, 0.022229897, 0.06526512, -0.076869376, -0.02514283, 0.025823941, -0.0038245246, -0.015392769, 0.0192346