41887026, -0.048806686, 0.045369517, -0.044572238, -0.02543507, 0.01732623, -0.01816914, 0.0141646005, -0.023971597, 0.01477689, 0.010868349, -0.017954951, 0.017345998, -0.014636828, 0.013097079, 0.011196291, 0.03272639, -0.026025482, 0.017049197, 0.007865691, 0.017587889, -0.030911317, -0.024049979, -0.037221476, -0.004339451, -0.017677326, 0.055854306, 0.03026148, 0.0057544126, -0.0036094475, -0.07364695, -0.014663649, 0.053123336, 0.015442922, -0.014211042, -0.06700198, 0.005197326, -0.00435949, -0.026100649, 0.09837351, -0.025554964, -0.004559274, 0.0090626, -0.027596975, 0.008551141, -0.020872727, -0.0140735665, 0.002071329, 0.035400707, -0.048659, -0.009520418, -0.09320614, -0.02670788, -0.036916554, -0.008832, -0.01901511, 0.02295644, -0.031748936, -0.0014142733, -0.025373943, 0.05135136, 0.06743958, -0.0037953726, 0.02717424, -0.0040230923, -0.042069945, 0.058676112, 0.026794981, -0.028972346, -0.008471729, 0.06223993, 0.05520604, -0.019739792, 0.052447863, -0.026571374, 0.033398144, -0.007467361, -0.045238215, -0.023971787, 0.005879938, -0.02945379], text:"been no investigation of how LRRK2 mRNA levels are regulated [33]. This work uncovered a novel\nmechanism of regulation of LRRK2 mRNA levels through adenine/uridine-rich element (ARE)-\nmediated mRNA decay (AMD) [33,78]. A purine biosynthesis enzyme ATIC and its substrate 5-\naminoimidazole-4-carboxamide ribonucleotide (AICAR; also known as ZMP) were found to regulate\nLRRK2 levels and affected LRRK2-induced DA neurodegeneration and neuroinﬂammation in PD an-\nimal models (Figure 4). Although the precise mechanism by which AICAR triggers AMD needs further\ninvestigation, this study provides a novel upstream mechanism for LRRK2 regulation through\nLRRK2 mRNA decay to reduce LRRK2 protein levels. This mechanism is distinct from the\nknown enzymatic functions of LRRK2 and suggests a novel avenue for targeting LRRK2.\nRegulation of LRRK2 protein stability\nSeveral studies have focused on the regulation of LRRK2 protein stability [31,79–82]. HSP90 forms\na complex with LRRK2, and inhibition of HSP90 chaperone activity leads to proteasomal degrada-\ntion of LRRK2 [31,82]. Furthermore, the E3 ligases CHIP, WSB1, and TRIM1 have been reported\nto ubiquitinate LRRK2, resulting in proteasomal degradation of LRRK2 and providing neuronal pro-\ntection [31,80,81]. TRIM1 recruits LRRK2 to the microtubule cytoskeleton where it mediates\nLRRK2 ubiquitination and proteasomal degradation, and also inhibits Rab29-mediated activation\nof LRRK2 kinase activity [81]. These ﬁndings suggest that cellular pathways that decrease\nLRRK2 protein levels are possible targets.\nDownstream substrates regulated by LRRK2\nIdentifying physiological substrates has been a major effort in studying LRRK2 kinase activity.\nLRRK2 has been reported to interact with and phosphorylate substrates involved in various\ncellular functions, including endocytic proteins such as endophilin A1 (EndoA) [83], synaptojanin\n(SYNJ1) [84,85], auxilin/DNAJC6 [86], and AP2M1 [87]. In addition, LRRK2 phosphorylates the", page:6}}, {_id:2530, properties:{chunk_index:2, id:"PIIS1471491424001898.pdf::p6::2::5c5c374e", embedding:[0.04961056, 0.06918529, -0.12508519, -0.017067483, 0.08038751, -0.07827326, -0.023116909, 0.0075903726, 0.01986069, -0.049817633, -0.047654394, 0.024987798, 0.08012461, -0.045661766, 0.017980525, -0.042162005, 0.035088606, -0.0464318, 0.018819818, 0.07514729, -0.018225161, -0.04772003, 0.019042647, 0.013262928, 0.07233934, 0.12121616, 0.026379725, -0.040783897, -0.040191565, 0.0299352, 0.033634834, -0.05976166, -0.032168373, -0.015029744, -0.0044163526, -0.044968635, 0.084023006, 0.021462984, 0.01086899, 0.005416239, -0.035339627, 0.04045274, -0.0018869962, -1.9229048E-4, -0.021406272, 0.002140287, -4.7312106E-4, 0.003814363, 0.027000476, -0.06537444, 0.082197905, 0.0044387924, -0.00544961, -0.055312354, 0.11664599, 0.017020388, -0.01306867, -0.026953494, 0.018776188, 0.033243004, 0.085251525, 0.06758519