9809526, -0.06103524, -0.012175651, -0.009799104, -0.04077604, -0.0024605652, 0.01048328, -0.0029782886, -0.02319387, 0.032096785, 0.07916518, 0.021619076, 0.017375864, 0.004980022, -0.028607879, 0.048628427, 0.025819954, -0.008795483, -0.020169415, 0.033541817, 0.06032045, -0.014634811, 0.03955571, -0.054680776, 0.051028896, -0.016627705, -0.042492673, -0.034093704, -0.029973423, -0.015903093], text:"cellular assay [89–91]. Rab proteins are major regulators of membrane trafﬁcking that inﬂuence\nprocesses ranging from endocytosis and Golgi trafﬁcking to autophagy/lysosomal biology, and\nmay therefore be implicated in the downstream cellular consequences of LRRK2 dysregulation\n(Figure 2). In this review we mainly focus on upstream regulation of LRRK2, but more details\nabout downstream substrates and related cellular consequences are given in Box 1.\nCellular consequences of altered LRRK2 regulation\nLRRK2 plays key roles in diverse pathways including the endolysosomal pathway, endoplasmic\nreticulum (ER) homeostasis, microtubule binding and cytoskeletal assembly, and mitochondrial\nfunction, as well as in cell non-autonomous functions, among others. Each pathway may contribute\nto LRRK2-induced DA neuron degeneration. DA neurons are notable for their high energy demand\nbecause they have long, branched, and unmyelinated axons. Disruption of trafﬁcking and commu-\nnication with neighboring cells, the accumulation of misfolded and aggregated proteins, failure of\nenergy production in mitochondria, and microglial neuroinﬂammation can all have adverse effects\non DA neuronal survival [92]. Because each pathway has been extensively reviewed by others,\nwe brieﬂy discuss the signiﬁcance and implication of the major pathways in which LRRK2\nis involved.\nEndolysosomal trafﬁcking\nThe ability of LRRK2 to phosphorylate several endocytic proteins and a subset of Rab proteins,\ncoupled with its recruitment to speciﬁc organelles such as the Golgi via Rab29, lysosomes via\nRab12, and to the pericentriolar region via Rab38, underscores its functional involvement in dif-\nferent organelles within the endolysosomal pathway (Figure 2). These substrates perform distinct\nfunctions at various steps in the pathway, raising the possibility that LRRK2 acts as a regulatory\nkinase for multiple proteins involved in endolysosomal trafﬁcking (Box 1). LRRK2-induced toxicity", page:7}}, {_id:2532, properties:{chunk_index:1, id:"PIIS1471491424001898.pdf::p7::1::dd4f3faf", embedding:[0.07304103, 0.083667904, -0.12378591, -0.0065628407, 0.07092127, -0.05390863, 0.0083117895, 0.02553168, 0.015818177, -0.021503406, -0.039044134, 0.0244426, 0.0925864, -0.025857799, -0.0033509873, -0.0524611, 0.030492464, -0.04722106, -0.008050531, 0.06298519, -0.06427967, -0.019452192, 0.0061734566, -0.03485263, 0.059667535, 0.1091746, 0.025443148, -0.014769676, 0.0014420873, 0.018143108, 0.0933939, -0.0518779, -0.033525884, -0.036105614, -0.08677376, -0.0587483, 0.088326015, 0.0510177, 9.603644E-5, 0.007906444, -0.0021104135, 0.029082105, 0.015017893, -0.036825653, -0.03131561, 0.015659116, 0.0015889155, -0.011238755, 0.03829745, -0.05984828, 0.078149326, -0.0011846537, -0.036103234, -0.041407198, 0.12969065, 0.030481085, 0.013081957, 0.00705816, 0.025602428, 0.032694872, 0.07278979, 0.07223008, -0.03723682, -0.007886561, 0.036751106, -0.047631726, -0.0041666315, 0.033965923, 3.7577076E-4, -0.032098304, 0.06727906, -0.019645924, -0.0022316722, 0.010102787, -0.028279634, -0.031471018, 0.024732172, 0.018689577, 0.014975448, 0.018958583, -0.022711894, -0.006156592, 0.068935, 0.031359885, -0.0022718827, 0.025857925, -0.07633076, -0.01367387, -0.015643174, 0.05788856, 0.0012500408, 0.017411271, 0.02853299, 0.036079314, -0.07384852, 0.07424607, 0.023865877, 0.033836674, -0.0047779772, 0.006528223, -0.008013849, -0.012275988, 0.020912506, -0.015730686, 0.009358474, 0.007989332, 0.06162099, -0.044853486, 0.021225035, 0.019165587, -0.03456918, 0.06252089, -0.043600705, -0.004736189, 