419363, 0.032459643, 0.01784769, 0.036430895, 0.009605634, -0.044205476, 0.015679736, 0.07186597, 0.009263817, -0.0024682258, -0.09777463, -0.0016455833, 0.042343203, -0.025442047, 0.08634778, -0.010002533, -0.008170631, 0.0050052325, -0.03284103, -0.013777206, -0.008960845, -0.010593173, -0.0040574567, 0.019022727, -0.040855613, -0.01708191, -0.08003562, -0.05521125, -0.02770568, 2.1697351E-4, -0.0030075351, 0.015263913, 0.0061410605, -0.003928589, -0.008917762, 0.0618674, 0.08384595, 0.0369354, 0.013165324, 0.03472487, -0.027492808, 0.06168565, 0.008976404, -0.0073898407, -0.04003405, 0.036568884, 0.045186162, -0.0205781, 0.034101933, -0.026670543, 0.014616591, -0.006249262, -0.031743735, -0.017569648, -0.021753363, -0.0049977186], text:"functions at various steps in the pathway, raising the possibility that LRRK2 acts as a regulatory\nkinase for multiple proteins involved in endolysosomal trafﬁcking (Box 1). LRRK2-induced toxicity\ncould result from a combination of various defects in this pathway. Interestingly, Rab29, Rab32,\nSYNJ1, auxilin/DNAJC6, and AP2M1 are also risk factors for PD [50,93–95].\nBox 1. Downstream LRRK2 kinase substrates and endolysosomal trafﬁcking\nLRRK2 phosphorylates several endocytic proteins, including EndoA [83] and its binding partner SYNJ1 [84,85], auxilin/\nDNAJC6 [86], and AP2M1 [87] (Figure 2). These substrates perform distinct functions at various steps in the endocytosis\npathway, including synaptic vesicle (SV) endocytosis. However, there is no general consensus on how LRRK2 affects\nprocesses at synapses. Further investigation is warranted to determine whether LRRK2 plays a direct role in SV trafﬁcking\nresulting from the phosphorylation of these substrates or whether SV trafﬁcking defects are far downstream effects\nindirectly related to other LRRK2 functions.\nThe identiﬁcation of a subset of Rab small GTPases as LRRK2 kinase substrates is a signiﬁcant advance in recent years\n[89–91] (Figure 2). Phosphorylation of Rab proteins by LRRK2 occurs in a tissue- or even cell type-speciﬁc manner, de-\npending on the abundance of the Rab proteins and the type of LRRK2 mutation. Rab10 is a substrate for all LRRK2-\nPD mutants in a cellular assay and its phosphorylation level is abundant in the lung but hardly detectable in the brain,\nwhereas Rab12 phosphorylation level is prominent in the brain [141]. In cells and tissues, LRRK2 G2019S increases\npS1292 autophosphorylation levels but has a mild effect on pRab10 levels, whereas LRRK2 R1441C or Y1699C displays\nmodest effects on pS1292 levels but markedly increases pRab10 levels [141]. This might be because different LRRK2 mu-\ntant proteins have distinct subcellular localizations which may affect their proximity to Rab10.", page:7}}, {_id:2533, properties:{chunk_index:2, id:"PIIS1471491424001898.pdf::p7::2::74410b49", embedding:[0.015126812, 0.07492178, -0.14660071, -0.03996058, 0.086986735, -0.010660739, -0.008523498, 0.007709062, -0.012358213, -0.01773166, -0.05321155, 0.07685528, 0.05741264, -0.015103313, 0.007945226, -0.04892899, 0.024718862, 0.013391038, 0.014147567, 0.031595174, -0.053959586, -1.2900589E-5, 0.02225411, -0.04633319, 0.04289584, 0.09905544, 0.027909985, -0.022233237, -0.01916301, 0.013767796, 0.085919894, -0.06432556, -0.03856938, -0.053979456, -0.044003516, -0.07170193, 0.09029861, 0.02792328, -0.020291034, 0.001177027, 0.01552234, 0.010088752, 7.4998377E-4, -0.053045858, -0.033456236, -0.0052810325, -0.03202731, -0.026242863, 0.03381294, -0.06701976, 0.043514423, 0.0074649923, -0.014418037, -0.05645969, 0.11174171, 0.0033113316, -0.018575277, -0.013497286, 0.0323991, 0.048048366, 0.060139578, 0.059168395, -0.06559738, 0.051753107, 0.019139657, -0.068512365, -0.010146144, 0.07131723, -0.011670796, -0.056069538, 0.022445401, -0.015907183, -0.002019386, 0.026800597, -0.037960853, -0.009003259, 0.02841844, -1.8514052E-5, -0.025437402, 0.033619538, -0.010668972, -0.016319722, 0.07792956, 0.02060034, 0.014370275, -0.0039484077