61, -0.03415474, -0.08012843, 0.010958196, 0.021395493, -0.024965743, 0.061596043, -0.04741273, 0.009196389, -0.020960234, -0.027880631, 0.017420927, 0.0013811943, -0.0020890653, -0.02989184, 0.048134364, -0.015360394, -0.030205877, -0.03277035, -0.034649983, -0.0340965, -0.019176345, -0.021471446, 0.010067179, -0.023106694, 0.0051080408, -0.01587454, 0.025822034, 0.054657333, 0.009083621, 0.012649985, 0.0115964115, -0.015023632, 0.054401405, 0.012381941, -0.0077225114, 0.010587734, 0.01743604, 0.051413495, 0.018650753, 0.032102063, -0.025637005, 0.052835654, 0.019813811, -0.014147806, -0.019642016, -0.029463954, -0.0054519465], text:"ER homeostasis\nThe function of LRRK2 in different organelles raises the question of which organelles impacted by\nLRRK2 are the most relevant to the disease. Among all cellular organelles, ER dysfunction is the\nmost understudied aspect of LRRK2 function. Some emerging studies have delved into the role of\nLRRK2 in the ER. The LRRK2 G2019S mutant has been reported to localize at the ER and\naccelerate ER stress through the regulation of sarco/endoplasmic reticulum Ca2+-ATPase (SERCA)\nactivity [96], as well as the SHP/PIAS1/XBP1 axis in astrocytes [97] and the interaction with THBS1/\nTGF-β1 in neurons [98]. LRRK2 also regulates ER–mitochondrial tethering through the PERK-\nmediated ubiquitination pathway [99]. The ER is a multifunctional organelle that plays crucial roles in\nproteostasis, including protein synthesis, folding, trafﬁcking, and degradation. Future directions may in-\nvolve investigating whether LRRK2 is involved in ER proteostasis and, in turn, contributes to the ac-\ncumulation of misfolded and aggregated proteins such as α-synuclein and glucocerebrosidase\n(GCase), a common feature of neurodegenerative diseases including PD.\nMicrotubule binding and cytoskeletal assembly\nThe interaction between LRRK2 and Rabs, particularly LRRK2 phosphorylation of Rab8a and\nRab10, has been linked to modulation of ciliogenesis [91,100] and centrosome cohesion [101]\n(Figure 2). Phosphorylated Rab8a and Rab10 by LRRK2 bind to lysosomal-like proteins 1 and\n2 (RIPL1/2) which are implicated in regulating ciliary membrane content. Centrioles – radially\norganized arrays of triplet microtubules – form the centrosomes and serve as the foundation for\nthe cilial basal body. These studies align with the discovery of LRRK2 binding to microtubules\nand the LRRK2-mediated regulation of the microtubule-binding protein tau [102,103]. Microtu-\nbules play vital roles in vesicular and organellar transport speciﬁcally in DA neurons, where", page:8}}, {_id:2535, properties:{chunk_index:1, id:"PIIS1471491424001898.pdf::p8::1::a0290ffd", embedding:[0.036982037, 0.059765864, -0.13385516, -0.022153152, 0.0827764, -0.034893498, -0.008713838, 0.012014347, -0.001786992, -0.048286505, -0.05478587, 0.036170326, 0.09586397, -0.028980123, -0.01750138, -0.030187208, -0.01691366, -0.02003353, -0.03404267, 0.01924041, -0.05407952, 0.024204832, -0.0011701554, 0.038018987, 0.06374968, 0.08897835, 0.021764109, -0.017965846, 0.03050819, 0.015021365, 0.11929549, -0.09859233, -2.23002E-5, -0.04791405, -0.05645363, -0.052327804, 0.0917758, 0.006386462, 0.006377033, 0.010773513, -0.011970439, -0.007526211, -0.061627746, -0.053549968, 0.024245616, 0.03541376, 0.017850759, -0.06214566, 0.045197435, -0.06576786, 0.06716225, -0.024539642, -0.011015746, -0.05355961, 0.12502384, -0.008878527, 0.040666673, 0.0025089388, 0.025297893, 0.03208613, 0.06777654, 0.08211829, -0.028717868, 0.04296298, 0.030424412, -0.028633736, -0.02795097, 0.027836839, -0.024359658, -0.01630974, 0.04424687, -0.0683386, 1.1551442E-4, 0.024848673, -0.0049592936, 0.019632889, 0.03435783, 0.0135127315, -4.7099692E-4, 0.007467638, -0.021300271, -0.009346074, 0.042789046, 0.0036143432, 0.018473703, 0.016882751, -0.05813782, -0.04293014, -0.0404759, 0.07771411, 0.012191403, 0.033333488, 6.98554E-4, 6.9812563E-4, -0.037996855, 0.027461039, -0.007945008, -0.015821032, -0