207, -0.03743959, 0.0046107094, 3.9092297E-4, 0.026235178, -0.04457488, -0.0014949609, -0.012733985, 0.046940256, 0.05203578, 0.005035591, 0.019797347, 0.018837273, -0.06456886, 0.025093364, 0.0033447642, 0.015385607, 0.0290335, 0.07306355, 0.086844444, 0.01456121, 0.011732248, -0.042728107, 0.018036611, -0.002192478, -0.050802793, 0.010524182, -0.03490638, -0.024933705], text:"notion that PD should be considered as a multisystemic disorder rather than as purely a brain\ndisease, aligning with the multiple-hit hypothesis of Braak.\nTargeting LRRK2 for therapeutic development\nClinical presentation of LRRK2-PD\nClinically, LRRK2-mediated disease is nearly indistinguishable from sporadic PD and has similar\nsymptoms, age of onset, and rate of clinical decline [3]. Pathologically, LRRK2 mutations consistently\ncause progressive degeneration of DA neurons in the SNpc. However, disease pathology including\nLewy body (LB) and tau-positive inclusions varies in carriers of different mutations [113–115]. Up to\n30% of G2019S carriers and 70% of other mutation carriers (R1441C/G, Y1699C, I2020T) did not\nshow LBs but 100% of carriers displayed tau pathology [113–115]. These ﬁndings raise the possibility\nthat disease progression occurs through divergent mechanisms. Given its status as the most com-\nmonly mutated protein in PD according to genetic studies, as well as its hyperactivation in disease\nmutants and the neuroprotective effects of small-molecule LRRK2 inhibitors in preclinical models,\nLRRK2 has emerged as a promising therapeutic target over the past 20 years [116–118]. Inhibition\nof LRRK2 activities and suppression of LRRK2 expression have been pursued as therapeutic ap-\nproaches for disease modiﬁcation [119]. Recent breakthroughs in elucidating LRRK2 protein struc-\nture provide precise structural bases for drug development [49,103,120,121].\nTargeting LRRK2 kinase activity\nIncreased LRRK2 kinase activity has been demonstrated in both familial PD and idiopathic PD\n(iPD) [6,35]. Consequently, the development of LRRK2 kinase inhibitors has been a major focus\nof drug development for PD therapeutics [116,118]. The most extensively tested inhibitors are\ntype I inhibitors that bind to the ATP pocket, representing the active and closed conformation of\nthe kinase. Highly potent, brain-penetrant, and selective compounds such as GNE7915, GNE-", page:9}}, {_id:2538, properties:{chunk_index:1, id:"PIIS1471491424001898.pdf::p9::1::e2a87606", embedding:[-0.044776093, 0.056176856, -0.12879254, 0.008213705, 0.052153967, -0.07781927, 0.030066757, 0.0013865437, -0.022975331, -0.027607683, -0.023625813, 0.040236868, 0.09473954, -0.05450733, 0.001684058, -0.057446085, 0.004959988, -0.045083642, -0.0030658348, 0.034273326, -0.06369391, -0.0059498623, -0.020494571, -0.03661988, 0.011718705, 0.061743993, 0.039173443, -0.036156505, 0.016300777, 0.043605417, 0.0942469, -0.088782035, -0.012249763, -0.029367257, -0.053250484, -0.03994048, 0.07535711, 0.06129338, -0.041236367, -0.017502226, 0.014010143, 0.03587908, 0.021350337, -0.035838462, 0.036431056, 0.024403546, 0.009732581, 0.01852098, 0.053551283, -0.06338314, 0.08619554, 0.0058093728, 0.0057999953, -0.04643884, 0.117013544, -1.9774321E-4, -0.04678751, -6.593308E-4, -0.025152262, -0.009539517, 0.03356067, 0.029155346, -0.014532553, 0.024665004, 0.04620406, -0.08046018, -0.044960365, 0.07531044, -0.027409261, -0.052544937, 0.06226859, -0.021939956, 0.03593878, 0.07444554, -0.029585253, 0.003794909, 0.026407422, -0.024542429, 0.0056728236, -0.030243365, -0.0028808247, 0.005139532, 0.07549942, 0.0031849327, 0.01625359, 0.043374207, -0.026712444, -0.00935576, -0.04694296, 0.047036212, -0.023576519, 0.010704195, -0.011428664, 0.016531637, -0.032435816, 0.04495573, 0.045739047, 0.0099157505, -0.048220884, 0.008002527, 0.019648677, 0.0017353601, 0.00836489, 0.03496139, 0.008154101, 0.013484675, 0.004303909, -0.027973182, 0.03091072, 0.021516718, -0.050772823, 0.05635576, -0.03525007, -0.05759972