77, 0.07906113, 0.0064306096, -0.04091443, -0.018093558, -0.014761317, -0.042356543, -0.051975023, 0.005664902, 0.017867465, -0.013876073, -0.0043886798, -0.012956991, -0.0040233633, 0.03024557, 2.9217798E-4, 0.03397555, -0.05231812, 0.03564151, -0.014572932, 0.025302824, 0.021184789, 0.016535118, -0.034022845, 0.027951514, 0.03780524, 0.0049320725, 0.016529715, -0.03162335, 2.4714466E-4, 0.02062648, 0.037641957, 0.030173935, 0.022775028, 0.065444365, -0.006264048, -0.082829304, 0.012998734, 0.032386865, 0.0025167242, -0.010263027, -0.06816079, -0.04454548, 0.010382029, -0.011978331, 0.027192952, -0.0068736672, 5.841983E-4, -0.006646822, -0.03071838, -0.03698087, -0.027067438, -0.017804075, -0.030735644, 0.021357767, -0.032899544, -0.010471056, -0.05719002, -0.024639364, -0.046236422, 0.018152216, -0.0073065856, 0.049601343, -0.009019402, 0.006876512, -0.010408556, 0.024588466, 0.027564116, -0.0076222266, 0.020811873, 0.049821056, -0.028800802, 0.01838696, -0.031957053, -0.003166634, 0.005231039, 0.0028314802, 0.09001013, 0.032586843, 0.054049045, -0.022059843, 0.018915286, 0.007415997, -0.03841562, -0.021255417, 0.006886765, -0.057444338], text:"AdoCbl, acts as a 'mixed-type allosteric inhibitor' of LRRK2 kinase activity. Unlike type I LRRK2\nkinase inhibitors, AdoCbl does not compete with ATP for the active site of LRRK2 and instead\ninduces a conformational change [128]. Although the concentrations of AdoCbl used in the study\nare high and may be a limitation for pharmacological treatment, AdoCbl represents a starting\npoint for the development of a new class of LRRK2 kinase inhibitors. Recently, nanobodies binding\nto different LRRK2 domains have also been designed to inhibit or activate LRRK2 through an allo-\nsteric mechanism [129].\nTrends in Molecular Medicine\n990\nTrends in Molecular Medicine, October 2024, Vol. 30, No. 10\nClinician's corner\nOn the safety side, PD is a chronic\ndisease. Thus, the safety proﬁle of\nlong-term dosing in aged and sick\nindividuals, who may have compro-\nmised lung function and immune sys-\ntems, is of utmost importance.\nOn the efﬁcacy side, the question is\nwhen and for how long LRRK2 drives\npathogenesis. What are the best\ntherapeutic windows of efﬁcacy, and\nwhat level of LRRK2 inhibition is safe\nand sufﬁcient to drive efﬁcacy in the\nclinic? Efﬁcacy would be in blocking\nat least half or more, but not all, of\nLRRK2 kinase activity or levels.\nRegarding target engagement, the ﬁeld\nstill does not have a good way to\nassess CNS LRRK2 target engage-\nment. The development of good bio-\nmarkers for measuring LRRK2 activity\nwill expedite a biomarker-guided clinical\ntrial. Phosphorylation of substrates\nsuch as Rab10 and LRRK2 autophos-\nphorylation at pS1292 have been\nused to measure target engagement\nin DNL151 clinical trials. Measuring\nLRRK2 expression could be achieved\nin circulating cells, CSF in the brain,\nand in urine to evaluate LRRK2 inhibi-\ntion. However, LRRK2 is not an abun-\ndant protein. Scalable and reliable\nassays still need to be developed.\nThe development of a ligand suitable\nas an LRRK2 positron emission to-\nmography (PET) tracer has not been\nvery successful.\nLRRK2\nmutations\nare", page:9}}, {_id:2542, properties:{chunk_index:3, id:"PIIS1471491424001898.pdf::p9::3::223fbe0a", embedding:[0.020054871, 0.050196968, -0.18048039, -0.02134007, 0.05732496, -0.005464981, -0.0026403582, 0.014334475, 0.012211552, -0.07070576, -0.0025233082, 0.07602691, 0.099247865, 0.0044774422, -0.01654594, -0.069582164, 0.039726384, -0.04994244, 0.00913588, 0.07507901, -0.03096469, -0.010681321, -0.024243237, -0.02879372, 0.028667063, 0.013465393, -0.0069473605, 0.012949919, 0.015960142, 0.017111422, 0.106093526, -0.04014208, -0.018314473, -0.038145762, 0.01657399, -0.075374484, 0.07465089, 0.0020224217, 0.017094618, 0.056261666, 0.015365441, -0.0034903488, -0.019213807, -0.052882064, -0.0046776426, 0.043228395, 0.020597266, 0.059258796, 0.03577171, -0.09109166, 0.056436785, 