 0.013878132, 0.026040325, 0.026643962, 0.052156232, -0.026280036, 0.0423641, 0.029028863, -6.3054916E-4, 0.0055568833, -0.006928564, -0.025373273, -0.0030051616, -0.050303806, -0.03582278, 0.021692988, -0.009276147, -0.03762029, -0.049586713, -0.019761192, -0.01931333, 0.013367992, 0.02638034, 0.031288125, -0.028312974, 0.05155531, -0.030812375, 0.027713267, -0.003148123, 0.0027444644, 0.032635298, 0.01681496, 0.016530396, 0.007964894, -0.023584627, -0.01613767, 0.013090045, 0.047445443, -0.005616614, 0.03168068, 0.008582897, 0.059237126, 0.043338843, -0.034878545, -0.008587191, 0.04254284, -0.0048756353, -0.02069369, -0.08746377, 0.0064661736, 0.015421818, -0.0032913443, 0.04966845, -0.06332472, -0.019401386, -0.005948616, -0.034454353, 0.0043506124, -0.008036637, -0.025346437, -0.023185045, 0.020432115, -0.021151438, -0.032503154, -0.035532013, -0.04598904, -0.049904235, 0.0011262877, -0.0076723658, 0.016809326, -0.050594613, -0.010299718, -0.027658008, 0.013741951, 0.031630933, 0.012265708, 0.019768836, 0.029587999, -0.06539356, 0.051573563, -0.010106555, -0.00823913, 0.026396403, 0.05230621, 0.07397516, -0.024807785, 0.044503003, -0.02811655, 0.04992413, 0.026980132, -0.042284377, -0.0045769685, -0.0016453103, -0.031246863], text:"We are witnessing an exciting time for the LRRK2 ﬁeld, although it has always been complex.\nLRRK2 lies at the nexus of signaling pathways and presents an attractive target. Although deﬁning\nboth upstream and downstream regulation of LRRK2 and revealing the fascinating cellular conse-\nquences of LRRK2 provide essential guidelines for therapeutic targeting, a few challenges in clinical\ntrials need to be addressed and several key questions remain to be answered (see Outstanding\nquestions). The central questions are still how LRRK2 is activated, why LRRK2 affects DA neurons\nTrends in Molecular Medicine\n992\nTrends in Molecular Medicine, October 2024, Vol. 30, No. 10\nOutstanding questions\nWhy is there incomplete penetrance\nof LRRK2 mutations? How do the\nenvironment and aging interact with\ngenetic factors to develop LRRK2-\nassociated PD and iPD?\nWhat are the immune and GI functions\nof LRRK2 versus its role in brain func-\ntion? What are functions of LRRK2 in\nneurons versus glial cells?\nWhich organelles impacted by LRRK2\nare the most relevant to the disease?\nWhat is the role of LRRK2 GTPase\nfunction, and how does it contribute to\nthe disease? What are the physiological\nGAPs and GEFs for LRRK2?\nHow does LRRK2 become activated?\nHow is LRRK2 recruited to different\nmembranes\nincluding\ndamaged\nlysosomes?\nWhy does LRRK2 affect DA neurons of\nthe SNpc in particular? Which cell\ntypes are most affected by LRRK2\ndysfunction?\nDo\nLRRK2\nmutations\ninduce\nα-\nsynuclein or Tau pathology in LRRK2-\nPD? What are the underlying divergent\nmechanisms?\nDo LRRK2 inhibitors have disease-\nmodifying effects in iPD patients?\nDoes\nLRRK2\ninteract\nwith\nother\nPD proteins or risk factors, speciﬁcally\nα-synuclein and GCase?\nWhy do LRRK2 mutations not induce\nsevere disease phenotypes in animal\nmodels?", page:11}}, {_id:2549, properties:{chunk_index:0, id:"PIIS1471491424001898.pdf::p12::0::0b0b8214", embedding:[0.04682336, 0.08242035, -0.13599008, -0.006597729, 0.083615154, -0.04593494, 0.03452624, 0.035503644, 0.03278909, -0.045017425, 0.007751005, 0.08931525, 0.092923075, 0.011705319, -0.0064223367, -0.041377615, 0.0016247676, -0.031530548, -0.043582916, 0.05809607, -0.04861101, 0.0049951696, -0.0069622663, -0.04511498, 0.04620091, 0.080820404, -0.008261905, -0.036609903, 0.04796119, 0.027078426, 0.1296378, -0.037258867, -0.0481839, -0.027790483, -0.029180067, -0.048794262, 0.09984026, 0.0448357, 0.02140518, 0.034047455, -0.0018209256, 0.025748665, 0.00395054, -0.048799314, 0.032475118, 0.063279554, 0.026354983, -0.004794374, 0.08106104, -0.09258365, 0.05807506, 0.002472289, 0.027879205, -0.052295323, 0.091856934, 0.008542211, -0.020336326, -0.014859147, 0.008565769, -0.028275598, 0.071