 necessarily \nthose of the National Health Service, the NIHR, or the Department of \nHealth. The figures were generated with biorender.com.\nReferences\n1\t\nBen-Shlomo Y, Darweesh S, Llibre-Guerra J, et al. The epidemiology \nof Parkinson’s disease. Lancet 2024; 403: 293–3-4. \n2\t\nVijiaratnam N, Simuni T, Bandmann O, Morris HR, Foltynie T. \nProgress towards therapies for disease modification in Parkinson’s \ndisease. Lancet Neurol 2021; 20: 559–72.\n3\t\nLewy FH. Paralysis agitans. I. Pathologische anatomie. \nIn: Lewandowsky M ed. Handbuch der Neurologie. Berlin: Springer \nVerlag, 1912: 920–33.\n4\t\nGibb WR, Lees AJ. The relevance of the Lewy body to the \npathogenesis of idiopathic Parkinson’s disease. J Neurol Neurosurg \nPsychiatry 1988; 51: 745–52.\n5\t\nGeddes JF, Hughes AJ, Lees AJ, Daniel SE. Pathological overlap in \ncases of parkinsonism associated with neurofibrillary tangles. \nA study of recent cases of postencephalitic parkinsonism and \ncomparison with progressive supranuclear palsy and Guamanian \nparkinsonism-dementia complex. Brain 1993; 116: 281–302.\n6\t\nKalia LV, Lang AE, Hazrati LN, et al. Clinical correlations with Lewy \nbody pathology in LRRK2-related Parkinson disease. JAMA Neurol \n2015; 72: 100–05.\n7\t\nDoherty KM, Silveira-Moriyama L, Parkkinen L, et al. Parkin \ndisease: a clinicopathologic entity? JAMA Neurol 2013; 70: 571–79.\n8\t\nWang J-L, Xiao B, Cui X-X, et al. Analysis of SCA2 and SCA3/MJD \nrepeats in Parkinson’s disease in mainland China: genetic, clinical, \nand positron emission tomography findings. Mov Disord 2009; \n24: 2007–11.\n9\t\nCaparros-Lefebvre D, Sergeant N, Lees A, et al. Guadeloupean", page:9}}, {_id:2795, properties:{chunk_index:4, id:"1-s2.0-S0140673623014782-main.pdf::p9::4::b4eca51a", embedding:[0.08389948, 0.08719443, -0.14914507, -0.046720956, 0.041828472, 0.019961586, 0.026144031, -0.012676289, 0.06599129, -0.053967364, 0.04721738, 0.047673933, 0.07719038, 0.0104673905, -0.048857953, -0.07891981, 