66, 0.07026936, 0.012640938, -0.00425287, 0.09831058, 0.038372096, 0.01772341, -0.03768464, -0.021091817, 0.0113777, 0.025455479, -0.057692014, -1.7396202E-4, -0.032472093, -0.0011515658, 0.01676796, -0.018456696, -0.028706823, -0.018461322, -0.018755157, 0.06934451, -0.019956466, -0.03463789, -0.0124662975, 0.055660304, 0.0020128952, -0.009209652, -0.0086733205, -0.021088334, 0.031871885, 0.055561494, -0.017346093, 0.075237155, -0.0113087585, 0.011280379, 0.009744174, 0.009332438, 0.01088688, -0.0051732776, -0.00964162, -0.013367895, -0.034970533, -0.02731756, 0.03823863, -0.044257507, -0.006744323, -0.002876946, -0.020139383, -0.050961427, -0.016839234, 0.020141788, 0.021366319, 0.014130924, 0.018255105, 0.0017029551, 0.042582735, 0.03576917, -0.021895649, -0.012551276, 0.015465382, 0.026228894, -0.02186162, 0.017600635, 0.025953786, 0.036317986, 0.013589238, 0.027806733, 0.038073946, 0.010971372, 0.02778152, 0.020716388, -0.10154774, -0.0141861625, 0.025401227, -0.018190186, -0.018609013, -0.07779835, -0.039627075, 0.041800477, 0.009447447, 0.10171155, -0.043538447, -0.011123025, -0.02726559, -0.04693935, -0.0106218485, -0.0023009826, 0.019824632, 0.012040167, 0.03667791, -0.045935653, -0.012493225, -0.06306664, -0.02097969, -0.030440232, -0.0025076037, -0.010860743, 0.012339135, -0.038539454, -0.0021738238, -0.025922313, 0.05729427, 0.07712185, 0.028106457, 0.029002797, 0.005617521, -0.033596534, 0.050679814, 0.023991661, -0.004301932, 0.021421114, 0.034125816, 0.09285352, -0.0021008141, 0.018037986, -0.05540425, 0.05966024, -0.027271803, -0.059201036, -0.022931261, -0.010277981, -0.009186649], text:"with disease duration [14], and that, validating the pioneering obser­\nvations of Burke and colleagues, the more Lewy pathology in the nigra, \nthe more nigral neurons remain [14]. \nOne historical variant of the gain-of-function proteinopathy hy­\npothesis posited that Lewy bodies represented an imbalance between the \nproduction of “unwanted proteins” and their degradation by the \nubiquitin-proteasome system in conjunction with heat shock proteins \n[15]. Olanow and colleagues conceived them as late “cytoprotective \naggresomes” to facilitate the capture and degradation of “excess \namounts of unwanted and possibly cytotoxic proteins.” [15] One could \nread into this that Lewy pathology formation is a good thing and should \nbe encouraged to ‘trap’ toxic proteins. \nLewy pathology has been conceived as having both neuroprotective \nand neurotoxic roles. Pathology is a state of protein structured as a beta- \npleated sheet. Such stability precludes it from having a function or \ninflicting toxicity. Hence, pathology is best conceived as a common \nresult of many biological processes and the beginning of none. In the \nsame way that lipofuscin accumulates with age but is not the cause of \naging we suggest that Lewy and other pathologies accumulate with age \nwithout accelerating or decelerating aging. \n1.2. Proteins have functions –losing proteins is consequential \nHistorically, the bar for the concept that neurodegeneration was \nabout a gain of toxic proteins should have been higher than the more \nintuitive premise: degeneration is about loss, including proteins and \nneurons. In PD, the levels of α-synuclein, the 42-amino acid isoform of \namyloid-β (Aβ42), total tau, and phosphorylated tau are low compared \nto healthy controls [16]. This loss occurs because soluble proteins mis­\nfold into insoluble, highly stable cross-β clumps, detectable at \npost-mortem by histopathological methods. It has been necessary to \n“embrace complexity” [17] to accept the idea that a depleted natural", page:2}}, {_id:2850, properties:{chunk_index:2, id:"1-s2.0-S1353802024000890-main.pdf::p2::2::b75ef334", embedding:[0.07430745, 0.0575849, -0.14025818, -0.058496326, 0.037555162, -0.004763375, 0.006198015, 0.049781516, 0.02574392, -0.008750885, -0.012910097, -0.016858425, 0.1290879, 0.021098938, 0.010051335, -0.08008304, -0.016735395, -0