397, 0.021298612, 0.03106208, 0.05809101, -0.031588692, 0.020810936, 0.016305227, -0.031265657, -0.044939123, 0.073749445, -0.021673495, 0.017783461, -0.005447883, -0.0868771, -0.01099897, -0.0051731397, -0.005771082, 0.03846175, -0.025953881, 0.022295507, -0.0412875, -0.046298552, -0.083462656, 0.003522892, 0.06763147, -0.07236616, 0.01684524, -0.052220773, -0.0026938696, -0.02614794, 0.025428848, -0.022356467, 0.064944156, -0.007324673, -0.014585041, 0.039875213, 0.026594412, -0.03412986, 0.024606852, -0.0038775085, -0.039139822, 0.034754585, 0.0822677, 0.020155841, -0.027495282, 0.10073819, 0.042825032, 0.0043694526, -0.051168844, -0.018565942, 0.034456287, 0.064915664, -0.07439694, -0.019481359, -0.05997077, -0.0025186304, 0.027709082, 1.4397434E-4, 0.0033026703, 0.008716283, 0.0024434743, 0.030957852, -0.04349296, -0.041450176, -0.00593726, 0.03270517, 0.0076948446, -0.0032230536, -0.017077273, -0.024543792, 0.023973199, 0.06507292, -0.010636563, 0.0503995, -0.01434195, -0.008591268, -0.03745751, 0.03248167, 0.013443828, -0.02059101, -0.0060835714, 0.035868697, -0.053913284, -0.012442338, 0.030707164, -0.04292787, 5.547389E-4, -0.029304104, -0.026502378, -0.010995655, 0.014245349, -0.010251677, 0.03651417, -0.02496331, 0.067478694, 0.011648642, 0.065534085, 0.02707937, -0.025133576, -0.008253762, 0.022892319, 0.02303832, -0.00654215, -0.004267127, 0.017892836, 0.036107637, 0.052726373, 0.027293736, 0.045075018, 0.01876308, 0.024095355, 0.023779841, -0.065569974, 0.013193619, 0.037066724, 0.03920807, -0.03974238, -0.05867789, -0.03181498, 0.010679055, -0.015862238, 0.076167166, -0.03232024, -1.6131603E-4, -0.031177823, 0.00913925, -0.022613747, -0.062924765, 0.017494189, 0.011267245, 0.036486305, -0.058004387, 0.0046613207, -0.07752215, -0.03837816, -0.04604269, 0.026899466, -0.0048319097, 0.042748455, -0.02769508, -0.0011020773, -0.019405259, 0.044493154, -0.0072247023, 0.008058578, 0.05027663, -0.005156019, -0.02115577, 0.02624175, 0.01694153, 0.019222965, -0.004394246, 0.0061101774, 0.05483006, -0.014442673, 0.030601611, -0.01133821, 0.05096526, 0.03534199, -0.07816083, -0.02337285, -0.035284784, -0.0043547344], text:"knocking down α-synuclein in aged rats [28] or aged non-human pri­\nmates [29], nigrostriatal degeneration and behavioral changes are \nobserved. The use of short hairpin RNA in adult rats to silence endog­\nenous α-synuclein led to a 50% loss of nigrostriatal neurons in the \nsubstantia nigra pars compacta and a corresponding loss of nigrostriatal \nterminals and dopamine concentrations within the striatum [30]. \nNotably, adding rat α-synuclein to knockdown aged rats can rescue their \nbehavioral and neurodegenerative phenotype [28]. The rescue of a \nphenotype through restocking a genetically silenced protein was also \nconfirmed in mice models of Alzheimer’s disease where the addition of \nsoluble Aβ42 restored the phenotype both in the absence (presenilin1 \n[PS1] and presenilin2 [PS2] double knockout mice) and presence \n(APP/PS1/Tau triple transgenic mice) of amyloid pathology [31]. Given \nthe many studies supporting a critical role of α-synuclein in neuron \nfunction and survival [32], knocking down its expression below a \ncertain level would be expected to be deleterious [33]. Its ubiquitous \npresence in the human body beyond the brain and the evolutionary \nredundancy with β- and γ-synuclein further attest to its importance. \n2.3. Myth 3. α-synuclein propagates in a prion-like manner \nA PubMed search “strain AND synuclein AND Parkinson’s disease” in \nJanuary 2024 yielded about 300 basic science publications, all within \nthe last 20 years. Adding “prion” as the fourth term narrows the search \nto 80 publications, all in the last 10 years. A strain is a term borrowed \nfrom virology. It is “a genetically stable virus variant that differs from a \nnatural reference virus in that it causes a significantly different, \nobservable phenotype.” [34] The strain, prion-like quality attributed to \nLewy pathology, which suggests that a specific pathology gives rise to a \nspecific disease, is the direct expression of the gain of toxic hypothesis", page:3}}, {_id:2854, properties:{chunk_index:2, id:"1-s2.0-S1353802024000890-main.pdf::p3::2::2bf4577a", embedding:[0.09521663, 0.06443193, -0.15215744, -0.059237637, 0.053675406, -0.01277089, -0.0028338535, 0.035099406, 0.06341929, -0.021370418, 0.004176354, 0.038204674, 0.12673347, 8.203332E-4, -0.050615307, -0.06942683, -0.047264256, -0.059179902, 0.0038235495, 0.04693173, -0.08625234, -0.031606376, 0.046398196, -0.0046166084, 0.024493301, 0.07662816, -0.055674795, -0.049410284, 0.0051375492, -0.009322072, 0.07436702, -0.027206859, -0.0180716, -0.01669576, -0.023237085, -0.089922085, 0.039919596, 0.056725975, 0.030081457, 0.0071757543, -0.008949923, 0.046432707, 0.031487994, -0.08359732, -0.046250563, 0.066194326, 0.005199643, -0.02175427, 0.02784143, -0.079181746, 0.067921214, 0.004538678, 0.0035578092, -0.053099453, 0.10126646, 0.043456927, -0.0016691097, -0.017128032, 0.049334895, 0.0027284652, 0.034007244, 0.07741128, -0.04745666, 0.012590548, 0.029224474, -0.03868413, -0.026675597, 0.023958368, 0.031922568, -0.052810486, 0.031849068, -0.025378078, -0.022539262, -0.0071422933, 0.009105017, 0.0031657962, 0.0063666045, 0.016509572, 0.011988947, 0.023941083, -0.007068522, 0.03509688, 0.036095425, 0.020484257, 0.04166846, 0.022062888, -0.041473176, -0.011439195, -0.019057278, 0.083363704, 0.023024112, 0.010959694, -7.045407E-4, -0.017072944, -0.08002942, -0.027482778, -0.011694879, 0.014513937, -0.06935317, -0.004052348, -0.04879067, -0.011837728, 0.033218894, -0.0051516155, 0.01042101, 0.020370368, 0.011899765, -0.022146728, 0.021967035, 0.019534666, -0.021066137, 0.051845606, -0.03788929, 5.428946E-4, 0.02353468, -0.061131436, 0.048121274, 0.010347719, 0.0017785423, 0.07749472, -0.017665122, -0.015182646, -0.024523666, 0.07700329, -0.026909925, 0.037794743, -0.015548421, -0.0011237785, 0.037234098, -0.017805973, 