3, -0.017167954, 0.05887909, -0.019655135, -0.028095603, -0.048138134, -0.013471419, 0.018722007, -0.017116489, -0.042339504, 0.007396857, -0.051733516, -0.047467053, 0.010296975, -0.012947303, -0.03551405, -0.02371736, -0.0716844, -0.04426558, -0.010872321, -0.021014564, 0.026824703, -0.041447997, -0.0057868157, 0.046301134, 0.02337286, 0.030106265, 0.0029043811, 3.7615298E-4, 0.04087329, -0.006899212, -0.014324479, -0.056625593, 0.05275894, -0.059387103, 0.0030195785, 0.015763415, -0.03554791, -0.016727732, -1.8554552E-4, -0.043352023, 0.040596504, -0.065634996, 0.03149725, -0.008093739, -0.03923821, -0.0096945455, 0.00931422, 0.040327717, -0.038520787, 0.01577109, -0.07265527, 0.018392298, -0.029317684, 0.05501077, -0.0682892, 0.0478938, 0.042861793, -0.011748279, 0.027780468, 4.4343746E-4, -0.034597993, 0.01209941, -0.01630521, 0.021266501, 0.0030395167, 0.067515485, 0.0116116945, 0.0054824734, 0.059953388, 0.020523446, 0.020137515, -0.046650216, -0.023481915, 0.011171464, 0.035757203, -0.05580461, -0.019901782, -0.048256114, -0.026318902, 0.034121636, -0.011244041, -0.04727128, -0.0013010993, -0.026800964, 0.04446881, -0.014552171, -0.020962862, -0.020963565, 0.04319823, 0.014899233, 0.0012640783, -0.030022092, -0.011688526, 0.029033724, 0.049897823, 0.001593276, 0.056316454, -0.01369034, 0.013562387, 0.022009881, 0.012557783, -0.006724077, -0.024352027, -0.02203059, 0.011856778, -0.028487207, -0.052744795, 0.01769058, -0.044099357, -0.013503271, -0.011017299, -0.023721227, -0.022802373, 0.026901765, -0.012951278, 0.02318487, -0.0026952303, 0.035334364, -0.0044149, 0.025601814, 0.015621794, -0.020876372, 0.0015193927, 0.003356024, 0.025650648, -0.005158227, 0.007426552, -0.014157247, 0.026440375, 0.029984295, 0.037700314, 0.031412926, -0.018594453, 9.4683206E-4, -0.015504129, -0.07706321, -0.028648835, 0.0375328, -0.0056925653, -0.032518428, -0.083963476, -0.025703283, 0.057998873, -0.011311566, 0.09750241, -0.040956877, 2.0917306E-4, -0.019043716, -0.026670806, 0.01967914, -0.0047771404, 0.019840024, -0.018822528, 0.035081595, -0.03397617, -0.01937553, -0.07106487, -0.021518638, -0.013905923, 0.019739836, -0.001210399, 0.007897194, -0.04031171, -0.035356775, -0.04428374, 0.090481356, 0.024478985, -0.0036132133, 0.0048695044, -0.013155945, -0.022573898, 0.030542647, 0.01872606, -0.019803734, -0.015176927, 0.06207131, 0.0909154, -1.2189731E-4, -0.024045454, -0.04005022, 0.05031665, -0.009402895, -0.06694676, -0.008290808, -0.017054863, -0.008392661], text:"Lewy pathology, which suggests that a specific pathology gives rise to a \nspecific disease, is the direct expression of the gain of toxic hypothesis \nimplicit in the Braak staging of PD: pathology was envisioned to actively \nspread from one region of the brain to another. Protofilament or fibrillar \npolymorphs of distinct morphology are viewed as capable of “propa­\ngating via prion-like conformational templating” with the same fidelity \nas viruses [35]. But proteins and viruses do not share common biology. \nNot only has the stability of different pathology conformations never \nbeen established, but the “strain-ness” of prions is only supported using \nsuch laboratory tools as differential resistance to disaggregation and \nproteolysis [36]. \nProteins precipitate, not replicate. Normal, soluble, monomeric \nproteins transform into abnormal, insoluble amyloids via nucleation, the \nsame mechanism that underlies the phase transformation of water into \nice, which follows the second law of thermodynamics [37]. No active \nreplication or “conformational template” is needed to explain why \nproteins become amyloids. A precise set of microenvironmental in­\ngredients (supersaturated concentration at a certain temperature and \npH) suffice to overcome the nucleation barrier and passively generate \ninfinitely heterogeneous fibers [38]. The same thermodynamically \nregulated process is behind the stochastic phase transformation of water \ninto ice, yielding infinitely heterogeneous snowflakes. In the same way \nthat we cannot use a snowflake’s architecture to determine where it \ncame from, we cannot hope to understand or classify neurodegenerative \ndiseases according to the shapes of fibrils found at autopsy (Fig. 2). \n2.4. Myth 4. Lewy bodies may not be toxic, but α-synuclein oligomers are \nWith pathology having a dubious association with degeneration or \nsymptoms and normal monomers incapable of causing disease, a ‘gain of", page:3}}, {_id:2859, properties:{chunk_index:3, id:"1-s2.0-S1353802024000890-main.pdf::p3::3::d64a23a6", embedding:[0.06747945, 0.08989292, -0.15598671, -0.07613495, 0.040903375, -0.010171359, 0.0038071289, 0.01327741, 0.056777906, -0.014167931, -0.007723531, 0.03610397, 0.13774446, 0.0025954247, -0.019900411, -0.056789078, -0.040346317, -0.0381728, -0.025160613, 0.027990155, -0.07335905, -0.020102305, 0.06051542, -0.040731955, 0.015787825, 0.09653365, -0.057627033, -0.030589642, -5.81437E-4, -0.0045249644, 0.08635893, -0.017131649, 9.4516866E-4, -0.017036842, -0.01954727, -0.040455524, 0.04316616, 0.042926636, 0.045060888, 0.008690327, -0.001424558, 0.032337055, 0.031320058, -0.06288281, 0.008282052, 0.077282056, 0.040788304, -0.018479459, 0.060456213, -0.07913395, 0.07099107, 0.006744223, 2.3565261E-4, -0.022220442, 0.0707499, 0.02709548, -0.023318639, -0.020433906, 0.046917804, -0.015361037, -2.611563E-4, 0.06444991, -0.050644748, 0.014083244, 0.02180138, -0.053745836, -0.03147682, 0.0022572845, 0.041452162, -0.05940126, 0.04480734, 0.0069403597, -0.0051007126, 0.019031208, -0.0011875362, -0.009707169, 0.01948556, 0.027029872, 0.0013649898, 0.021597693, 0.023486221, 0.021443477, 0.037527777, 0.012415976, 0.04791653, 0.012428293, -0.019091604, 0.006937794, -0.02639446, 0.076852895, -0.0071761245, 0.018276585, -0.003215951, -0.007984399, -0.083397605, -0.008040925, -4.881227E-4, 0.021527331, -0.09087163, 0.014668026, -0.043901257, 0.014806219, 0.028478147, 0.020474108, 0.039119344, 0.042463854, 0.002040