0.006457045, -0.012203162, 0.0030599348, 0.002529954, 0.0066860993, -0.024809588, -0.017525502, -0.02752463, 0.00809321, 0.018442774, 0.021110632, 0.030616516, -0.013884313, -0.047486458, -0.0073511386, -0.027634636, -0.056985117, 0.0014582595, -0.030420888, -0.07794118, 0.022625713, -0.06086415, 0.045388818, -0.022535264, 0.019043917, -0.01710238, -0.0071620205, -0.06881447, -0.03880378, -0.069561, -0.029627798, -0.020177841, 0.0069592474, -0.020746682, 0.01943857, -0.041394036, 0.005286938, -0.046156522, 0.013884512, 0.033273835, 0.044595934, -0.004587969, -0.02318409, -0.020006659, 0.010330895, -0.011228235, -0.0036866942, 0.031283256, -0.040717393, -0.03925795, 0.007467767, -0.030196164, 0.025974665, 0.05449335, 0.020540971, -0.029268388, -0.056814767, -0.019332802, 0.03084771, -0.060714398, -0.026086638, -0.0016336298, -0.016839165, -0.06839291, -0.014198763, 0.011539657, -0.06374474, -0.020282757, -0.045486532, -0.067866966, 0.008606869, -0.001166032, 0.032537118, -0.04542308, -0.026668092, 0.034881867, -5.4967206E-4, 0.013552296, 0.01697826, 0.004196344, 0.039191876, -0.027025254, -0.009061877, -0.00604639, 0.016490335, -0.06325867, 0.04496298, -0.016143085, -0.012049279, -0.01594509, 0.022070723, -0.006079177, 0.05534075, -0.05198459, 0.019781256, -0.020593978, -0.010654534, -0.040097255, -0.0024858129, 0.035384875, -0.060835443, 0.022345636, -0.06717749, -0.0016551063, -0.04421076, 0.027536776, -0.023430878, 0.04450491, 0.02996912, 0.040529165, 0.029897647, 0.040836558, -0.030556845, -0.0019010162, 0.012667076, -0.0117077725, 0.021404142, 0.06349217, 0.025314119, -0.018652044, 0.08450041, 0.049039558, 0.011895403, -0.020102864, 0.010673783, 0.021336332, 0.020154217, -0.0285056, -0.022017585, -0.04073568, -0.024839899, 0.0206955, -0.0267505, -0.005147311, -0.023271916, -0.031609807, 0.035986666, 0.0076840227, -0.0032965497, -0.060719214, 0.081654795, 0.013290575, -0.036660623, -0.04296952, 0.008814855, 0.022016684, 0.06689461, -0.0052626436, 0.03810819, -0.041558772, -0.003926042, -0.009531151, 0.020678548, -0.004104509, 0.0076044234, -0.025063166, 0.0018570819, 5.0054723E-4, 0.020035947, 0.012651426, -0.042608358, -0.005076023, -0.029678468, -0.04787453, -0.0073432936, 0.011998404, 0.03115187, -0.0049105166, -0.045241904, 0.02800327, -0.02247229, 0.022376595, 0.010574131, 0.0074864584, 1.7926226E-4, -0.021292904, -0.015129559, -0.0064820335, -0.044332925, -0.050376654, 0.024531718, 0.012988609, -0.0053669047, 0.04569974, 0.01722114, 0.026938198, -0.03209182, -0.058543146, -0.016148025, 0.054420672, 0.04269739, -0.042089473, -0.11270699, -0.045493413, 0.026292266, -0.028620012, 0.071455, -0.01745682, 0.0038970734, -0.03425056, 6.604627E-4, -0.02014562, -0.022854052, 0.02670743, -0.014377522, 0.010623653, -0.0108866235, -0.05079516, -0.084154114, -0.03431189, -0.0621851, -0.004285343, 0.027036408, 0.0077169365, -0.0179676, -0.0069473754, -0.031246362, 0.100416675, 0.025809357, -0.029785164, 0.026135001, -0.012841553, -0.007915954, 0.012767419, -0.0017613795, -0.0018626435, 0.007377105, 0.04282445, 0.12085247, -0.050087832, 0.009321413, -0.0561087, 0.020677013, -0.0050491197, -0.058991276, -0.01548215, -0.01158399, -0.028050734], text:"Parkinsonism and Related Disorders 122 (2024) 106077\n4\n2.5. Myth 5. A positive seed amplification assay indicates proteins seed in \nthe brain \nSeeding is one of three nucleation mechanisms by which proteins \nundergo a phase transformation from liquid to solid, that is, from soluble \nto insoluble. A seed is a protein in an aggregated state, usually a fiber or \namyloid clump. The seed amplification assay (α-Syn-SAA) or real-time \nquaking-induced conversion (RT-QuiC) are tests that harness the phys­\nics of seeding to identify tissue containing aggregated α-synuclein. Su­\npersaturation is required for a seed to catalyze seeding (Fig. 3). The \nseeding test relies on a reagent made of monomeric α-synuclein at a \nconcentration 100,000,000 higher than it is physiologic in the human \nCSF, which is measured in mg/mL rather than pg/ml. The supersatu­\nration of the α-Syn-SAA or RT-QuiC creates the thermodynamic condi­\ntions favorable for the nucleation of α-synuclein around any seed in the \ntissue provided. The enhanced fluorescence of amyloid-binding dye \nthioflavin T (ThT) makes the catalyzed amyloid formed detectable, \nmaking it a “positive” test. Since aggregated α-synuclein is a common \ndenominator in most PD subtypes, a positive α-Syn-SAA/RT-QuiC is \nhighly correlated with a clinical diagnosis of PD [44,45]. But the \nsupraphysiologic conditions that make the seeding test excellent to \ndetect the presence of aggregated α-synuclein in the laboratory is the \nreason a positive result does not demonstrate pathogenesis, staging, or \nbiology of PD in humans. Also, as the seeding test provides a binary \nyes/no answer to the question, \"Is there aggregated α-synuclein in this \ntissue?\" but does not quantify the levels of aggregated proteins, nor of \nthe soluble monomeric precursor left in the tissue tested, it cannot be \nused to assess the severity or progression of disease [44], monitor \nresponse to treatments, or biologically subtype patients for future neu­", page:4}}, {_id:2861, properties:{chunk_index:1, id:"1-s2.0-S1353802024000890-main.pdf::p4::1::f6abe06e", embedding:[0.10772393, 0.08132934, -0.1378525, -0.045507688, 0.04887142, -0.0027171604, 0.027866047, 0.04914916, 0.059710816, -0.016222233, 2.3739543E-4, -9.3621854E-4, 0.087594815, -0.0053442637, -0.027304692, -0.08140855, -0.018492635, -0.03739568, -0.009903886, 0.03588808, -0.07541423, -0.015156191, 0.045227684, -0.0029852504, 0.03541509, 0.08616301, -0.08321829, -0.020412937, -0.0031885435, 5.05108E-4, 0.06803812, -0.026762342, -0.018875632, -0.024345653, -0.01790603, -0.064589344, 0.035730764, 0.039925512, 0.013996254, 0.024949597, -0.002407902, 0.049201306, 0.030926697, -0.06725253, -0.022401331, 0.052734673, -3.8454527E-4, -0.036134258, 0.07602855, -0.07749326, 0.0507