31995, 0.03257104, 0.0030136798, -0.10026975, -0.005667558, -0.025515608, -0.04318832, -0.013945912, -0.03592465, 0.019972961, -0.026587967, 0.0029665155, -0.037490606, -0.017469222, 0.046555743, -0.024169765, 0.02018882, -0.03332223, -0.012407914, -0.02848345, -0.0053914897, -0.027535826, 0.005910533, -0.005761624, 3.902521E-4, 0.014929818, -0.012519723, -0.018626891, 0.032985304, 0.028504156, 0.027149422, 0.011363371, 0.0867085, -0.010041156, 0.012539431, 0.084967755, 0.04120828, -0.013322291, -0.031396616, -0.008666513, -0.006826886, 0.02027256, -0.031311613, -0.012520636, -0.022154465, -0.015923683, -6.9076533E-4, 0.015852287, -0.02321461, -0.035391103, -0.044505186, 0.03745502, -5.397513E-4, 0.004354423, -0.030653939, 0.025871173, 0.016666492, -0.043352377, -0.041784003, 0.030155156, 0.044892553, 0.058846217, 0.0030213068, 0.056278206, -0.023864357, -0.008891659, 0.008450507, 0.045911193, 0.019575004, -0.03527872, 0.0079290485, -0.016577225, -0.03000097, -0.013238742, 0.008267772, -0.051636383, -0.04778966, -0.0024064833, -0.0077444734, 0.009028899, -0.005827265, -0.023358867, 0.03584784, -0.032348234, 0.023444418, -0.04724633, 0.037172984, 0.022900667, 0.010328459, -0.0026262577, 0.042348426, -0.010636043, 0.003977409, 0.008142276, -0.025597023, -0.017419817, 0.017725425, -0.015240933, 0.028247915, 0.0011195889, 0.02788795, -0.053566553, -0.09532956, -0.026745155, 0.027570516, 0.011652642, -0.020828128, -0.07657561, -0.06107669, 0.038804423, -0.028487982, 0.08422545, -0.061119266, -0.007459538, -0.027839461, -0.027159512, -0.021217326, -0.033692285, 0.006289623, -0.0029092275, 0.014497626, -0.029554393, -0.010202877, -0.091639385, -0.015549378, -0.034656867, -0.01011436, -0.0033637674, 0.019793795, -0.028444165, 0.0063562877, -0.007743337, 0.06224392, 0.019272877, -0.017003667, 0.02753028, -0.005758231, -0.06373433, 0.032283973, 0.006759724, -0.020827703, 0.0024164543, 0.0015724772, 0.11173426, 6.195408E-5, 0.008120486, -0.04947, 0.0447902, 0.018445553, -0.024773872, -0.021645717, -0.003550746, -0.040101435], text:"antibodies telling us something that the prior sixteen antibodies that \nsignificantly lowered brain amyloid couldn’t? It turns out that, through \nan unknown mechanism, most anti-amyloid monoclonal antibodies in­\ncrease the soluble levels of Aβ42. Lecanemab does it far above most \nothers: by nearly 300 pg/ml [49]. (The donanemab trial protocol did not \ninclude measures of CSF biomarkers.) That an anti-amyloid therapy \nmight exert any beneficial effect by increasing CSF Aβ42 poses a \nparadox. Does the end of increasing the soluble protein levels above a \ncompensatory threshold justify the means of removing amyloid? Amy­\nloid clearance results in brain swelling or bleeding in one of four \nlecanemab-treated patients and, like most other anti-amyloid treat­\nments, accelerates degeneration [51]. While only two negative phase 2 \ntrials of anti-synuclein monoclonal antibodies have been reported to \ndate [52,53], there remains a vigorous research pipeline of \nanti-synuclein therapies [54], encouraged further by the idea that a \npositive α-Syn-SAA/RT-QuiC “biologically” defines, stages, or classifies \nPD [55,56]. Might the field of PD continue to be inspired by the synu­\ncleinopathy hypothesis until it finds its own lecanemab? [57]. \nThe case of transthyretin amyloidosis and TTR silencing/stabilizing \ntherapies. Because of their high stability and low reactivity, amyloids \npose little direct toxicity unless they act as a mass-occupying lesion via \nextracellular matrix deposition of amyloid fibrils locally or systemically \n[58]. This is the case of transthyretin amyloidosis, in which the trans­\nthyretin (TTR) protein, coded by TTR and produced by the liver, phase \ntransforms into amyloid. Sufficient amyloid infiltration within the heart, \nin the case of cardiac amyloidosis, can impair its mechanical contrac­\ntility, leading to heart failure. This has led to the development of TTR \nsilencing or stabilizing therapies designed to lower the TTR protein", page:5}}, {_id:2871, properties:{chunk_index:2, id:"1-s2.0-S1353802024000890-main.pdf::p5::2::26cd54ac", embedding:[0.06500041, 0.07429155, -0.15320791, 0.0054188995, 0.06492762, -0.021920478, 0.016428472, 0.026354842, 0.026771836, -0.031168057, -0.002590583, 0.018715942, 0.10283681, -0.023016598, 0.01789519, 0.010652217, 0.023784777, -0.031155206, -0.033577442, 0.029244019, -0.06552626, -0.021478213, -0.025963092, 0.0080328435, 0.053072907, 0.10756937, -0.0605124, 0.02535639, -0.023452785, 0.038256034, 0.09156793, -0.0688866, 0.01279254, 0.025575504, -0.052453127, -0.071666375, 0.061703794, 0.07076013, 0.02246843, 9.67035E-6, 0.014418538, 0.043697145, 0.027180469, -0.047263935, 0.039360505, 0.028144231, 0.028631303, 0.02691053, 0.0494666, -0.068667285, 0.058517538, -0.037115328, -0.046141732, -0.02841419, 0.067593604, -0.0031320525, -0.055025738, -0.023878563, 0.023028627, -0.04358337, 0.061507866, 0.08659229, -0.055312105, -0.004215531, 0.07412471, -0.07119297, 0.0023522016, 0.04422531, 0.02389794, -0.006612502, 0.03373919, 0.0112404805, 0.0054260357, 0.025541272, -0.02052582, 0.010080536, -0.008030909, -0.013412827, 0.0054037217, 0.04883956, 0.0022778749, 0.004555136, 0.036981076, 0.03653432, 0.034904376, 0.009730813, 5.753897E-4, -0.02595132, -0.012260014, 0.095250405, 0.031611584, 0.006819106, 0.0032181176, -0.0103590945, -0.034369905, 0.020140035, 0.028761689, 0.011452895, -0.031122623, -0.0053319633, -0.03817941, -0.011750993, 0.01628902, -0.015333213, -0.0061260103, 0.01901582, 0.06005286, -0.0148000065, -6.092994E-4, 0.017647898, -0.040210254, 0.03314871, -0.029358968, -0.029611116, -0.02250076, -0.03131751, 0.025846753, 0.008033746, 0.0029940172, 0.002903658, -0.009547998, -0.0072969203, -0.00441937, 0.058126744, -0.0022373158, 0.02750891, -0.055720326, 0.021682756, 0.049185883, -0.066061914, -0.037603777, 0.004639818, -0.033940308, -0.0059522963, -0.0537647, 0.077227734, -0.046284854, -0.016602667,