4126, 0.048006516, -0.0555379, -0.009677818, -0.019936563, -0.018299114, -0.0029129481, 0.015186722, -0.003288554, -0.05486063, -0.009374546, -0.04901688, -0.02947934, -0.01212592, -0.031003095, 0.043687794, -0.06226178, -0.03913921, 0.031411797, 0.0452163, 0.006331783, 0.033724137, -0.01102474, 0.054508887, -0.015356997, 0.019749233, -0.022688672, 0.045491204, -0.06430905, 0.033158407, 7.0239895E-4, -0.08148271, 0.0066754557, -0.034351014, -0.09192645, 0.055848736, 0.0011130935, 0.050920777, 0.0041766074, 0.006315964, -0.047756094, -0.011568869, 0.049309604, -0.030899627, 0.020296713, -0.039453287, 0.01579106, -0.017722836, 0.03179761, -0.013718282, 0.010644029, -0.0048637805, -0.0022570998, 0.013162414, 0.006578556, -0.007857245, 0.015853396, 0.018795893, 0.025443112, 0.024715623, 0.06738278, -0.00709039, 0.030679772, 0.119313, 0.06709365, 6.192209E-4, -0.0076150387, 0.0087785395, 0.0035836534, 0.010821964, -0.045993447, -0.03922267, -0.056277372, -0.0071340357, -0.0051107067, 0.0141056515, -0.021838916, -0.01795846, -0.0067319605, 0.0062465183, -0.012301696, -0.031154647, -0.013781626, 0.04768773, 0.032752763, -0.0260993, -0.034444716, 0.020830175, 0.04185823, 0.04593791, -0.038793374, 0.04690478, -0.030929592, -0.020622766, -0.046497453, 0.037229322, 0.0022656263, 0.015290698, 0.011313184, -0.0012485856, -0.026499592, -0.025645833, 0.020576585, -0.049243856, -0.032593325, -0.004036504, -0.019336272, 0.012303887, -0.016185783, -0.009588039, 0.060966834, -0.035983883, 0.041251883, -0.031694546, 0.04084846, 0.033967115, 0.004986664, 0.01237843, 0.007212395, -0.0145304715, -0.012233553, -0.014174365, -0.0104602, 0.009622255, 0.032397084, 0.0400838, 0.029894678, 0.01810001, -0.007276498, -0.02502211, -0.09869517, -0.008665157, 0.04905017, 0.028035814, -0.06943115, -0.061365336, -0.06445896, 9.989989E-4, -0.041737918, 0.057042386, -0.040410303, -0.024269026, -0.054849237, -0.022044798, -0.02087149, -0.0317081, 0.015868656, 0.011878053, -4.5302542E-4, -0.0575712, -0.038396474, -0.09771961, -0.018008957, -0.03855837, -0.002014013, -0.0042127674, 0.012544916, -0.02622305, 0.019420225, -0.0035143916, 0.069205716, 0.028370019, -0.013291328, 0.026878305, 0.030951403, -0.046840962, 0.026692932, 0.0056752376, -0.026667774, 0.008576266, 0.011112349, 0.10166642, -0.017666612, 0.039172154, -0.04329958, 0.0044211377, 0.02263282, -0.06145117, -0.035291016, -0.0070091938, -0.03936643], text:"tility, leading to heart failure. This has led to the development of TTR \nsilencing or stabilizing therapies designed to lower the TTR protein \nlevels to prevent their transformation into amyloid. However, lowering \nTTR is problematic since this small tetrameric protein is necessary for \nbinding and transporting thyroxine (T4) and retinol (vitamin A) to tis­\nsues [59]. In fact, TTR variants that lower transthyretin concentrations \nincreased the incidence of heart failure [60]. Patients with lower base­\nline serum TTR levels exhibit shorter survival, with decreasing TTR \npredicting worsening cardiac function [61]. A mechanism by which TTR \nstabilizers \nmay \nreduce \nmortality \nand \ncardiovascular-related \nhospitalizations is by increasing serum TTR levels, as shown in a \ndose-dependent fashion in the tafamidis trial [62]. Direct genetic \nsilencing of TTR with patisiran, an RNA interference agent, and ino­\ntersen, an antisense oligonucleotide, both of which reduced serum TTR \nlevels by 80%, modestly improve function (e.g., patisiran lowered the \n6-min walk test [primary endpoint] at 12 months by 14.4 m [63]; below \nthe minimal clinically important change, 33 m [64]), but also increase \nthe rate of sudden cardiac death and heart failure compared to controls \n[65]. It bears noting that Lewy pathology, the amyloid state of α-synu­\nclein in PD, has no measurable effect on brain volume or function. Lower \nlevels of monomeric α-synuclein but not higher levels of pathologic \n(amyloid) α-synuclein predict faster progression [66]. This further \nlessens the rationale for anti-protein therapies. \nThe synucleinopenia hypothesis is testable and falsifiable. If a \nfuture clinical trial demonstrates that elevating the levels of soluble \nα-synuclein does not improve overall function, slow or halt progression, \nor meaningfully change biomarkers of structural integrity (Fig. 4), this \nhypothesis can be rejected. But to test this hypothesis, research in­", page:5}}, {_id:2875, properties:{chunk_index:3, id:"1-s2.0-S1353802024000890-main.pdf::p5::3::7cfb563e", embedding:[0.0756152, 0.064688325, -0.14517799, -0.042852692, 0.044515673, 0.0016765248, 0.015105537, 0.059969548, 0.06144729, -0.016764848, 0.029924423, -0.0013781176, 0.07220082, 0.034758374, -0.0023207131, -0.03223887, -0.046907634, -0.040730067, -0.00852373, 0.027894668, -0.0628237, -0.029849708, 0.04131573, -0.009417759, 0.033481263, 0.09125004, -0.051527902, -0.011509708, 0.012033144, 0.02528671, 0.107436016, -0.03535145, 0.010352849, -0.018126184, -0.04675802, -0.056167047, 0.04560345, 0.051257536, 0.019889005, -0.0032480906, 0.004893008, 0.038872637, 0.029787868, -0.047150265, 0.02472294, 0.060872063, 0.061644424, -0.035235684, 0.1010192, -0.09889192, 0.03382542, -0.023697715, -0.007099735, -0.03206451, 0.08681006, 0.025470663, -0.003513719, -0.03656432, 0.033225678, -0.03647942, 0.05410072, 0.072480164, -0.061630704, -0.005601142, 0.030162344, -0.048488434, -0.020799184, 0.0319734, 0.0053988127, -0.07583623, 0.035048384, -0.0020999387, 0.015375293, 0.02690041, -0.0073227803, 0.004453418, 0.018113555, 0.015564644, 0.004440485, 0.018103957, 0.025970858, 0.0027944902, 0.06322378, 0.054169208, 0.040664617, 0.004811204, -0.02089478, -0.0067419135, -0.023364775, 0.08632786, 0.04859245, -0.020632988, -0.012750211, -0.017337957, -0.051354565, -0.016972132, 0.018236943, 0.021330899, -0.07248286, -0.0031203781, -0.052138556, 0.013179358, -0.008957314, 0.0018996459, 0.019462777, 0.02420694, 0.03994009, 0.008756645, 0.0073579308, 0.01540383, -0.047625557