0.034163434, 0.032878533, 0.018053202, 0.04108106, 0.009276408, 0.005892883, -0.011005577, -0.099504, -0.007959706, 0.025408996, -0.012559195, -0.044390835, -0.09028967, -0.020708073, 0.049559943, -0.019738294, 0.080629446, -0.05807178, -0.0045246086, -0.035248905, -0.0117753735, -0.00282172, -0.02528585, -0.024089279, -0.007926435, 0.022657035, -0.046418857, -0.026551807, -0.09935234, -0.032642715, -0.064242885, 0.0092024235, -3.8082642E-4, 0.028036444, -0.041581657, 0.00231309, -0.004278506, 0.03998725, 0.01069775, -0.01575554, 0.042068787, 0.009994197, -0.046360865, 0.04557107, -0.025917724, 0.0062830606, -0.006254568, 0.01239459, 0.08566548, -0.0072710025, 0.025692705, -0.013248818, 0.05081901, -0.0063913544, -0.063142724, -0.024005327, -0.012872194, -0.0053510754], text:"or meaningfully change biomarkers of structural integrity (Fig. 4), this \nhypothesis can be rejected. But to test this hypothesis, research in­\nvestments must diversify resources from their current focus on anti- \nα-synuclein interventions. It can be argued that the risk of strategies \ndesigned to enhance monomeric α-synuclein is that the brain may end \nup with more Lewy pathology. As pathology bears no correlation with \nsymptoms or degeneration, this risk should be low and of a magnitude \nnowhere like that of anti-amyloid monoclonal antibodies, which in­\ncludes brain swelling and bleeding. Pathology is the “messenger” of a \nnormal brain reacting against something that shouldn’t be there, not the \nsource of toxicity. \n5. Conclusions \nThere are many causes for the loss of α-synuclein, reflected in the \nphenotypic diversity of PD. We have avoided conflating “origin” (of PD \nsymptoms) with “cause.” While precision medicine will require an un­\nderstanding of what makes Jim’s PD different from Mary’s and George’s \n– so that we can treat their diseases in a biologically sensible, individ­\nualized manner – there remains an opportunity to harness the principles \nof rescue medicine, restoring the levels of α-synuclein, compromised \nsimilarly in Jim, Mary, and George. \nLewy pathology is formed from previously normal, monomeric sol­\nuble α-synuclein. Once transformed into pathology, any function \nα-synuclein had is lost. Pathology, therefore, represents the end of \nfunctional α-synuclein rather than its conversion into a virus- or prion- \nlike agent. Clearing pathology cannot restore the health of a degener­\nating brain any more than clearing tree stumps can restore the health of \na dying forest. But restoring deficient nutrients to the diseased brain \nmight lead to the formation of green shoots and reforestation. Shifting \ndisease-modifying efforts from protein clearance to protein replacement \nwill require a shift in the overall paradigm in neurodegeneration from a", page:5}}, {_id:2876, properties:{chunk_index:4, id:"1-s2.0-S1353802024000890-main.pdf::p5::4::6a795a02", embedding:[0.08088294, 0.06970962, -0.12756963, -0.039283033, 0.044715624, -0.01504175, 0.016965004, 0.029246269, 0.059353575, -0.02201304, 0.031777516, 0.012601929, 0.057780918, -0.0027655696, 0.0451568, 0.008884182, -0.017712416, -0.057187635, -0.04370379, 0.04140588, -0.05436697, -0.012482255, -0.009325595, -0.035320327, 0.036283262, 0.072376505, -0.05911764, 0.010267667, -2.9669082E-4, 0.025928179, 0.06415774, -0.030127827, -0.050942812, 0.007801619, -0.023392757, -0.02078496, 0.098778635, 0.017440366, -0.01871225, 0.002470137, 0.004218082, 0.042375352, 0.028070832, -0.07595135, 0.035087887, 0.04682982, 0.017171353, -0.07088167, 0.008376397, -0.09352118, 0.046264295, 0.021309776, 0.003979441, -0.020808673, 0.09579709, -0.0038597458, -0.028123239, -0.035461325, 0.0120042935, -0.03318785, 0.09962704, 0.10440518, -0.043018334, 0.03328791, 0.07284631, -0.066082805, -0.025258869, 0.03579762, 0.0151176, -0.052265044, -0.018904569, 0.008809032, 0.009395009, 0.040970944, 0.0037134867, -0.016030924, -0.01990781, 0.01705228, -0.031454492, 0.02334365, -0.03942243, 0.011884018,