lucocere-\nbrosidase activity (Rizig et al. 2023).\nGenetic Risk Factors Contributing\nto Complex PD\nOver 80% of patients are affected by nonmono-\ngenic, complex PD arising from the interplay of a\nA. Westenberger et al.\n12\nCite this article as Cold Spring Harb Perspect Med 2025;15:a041774\nwww.perspectivesinmedicine.org\nPress \n on November 10, 2025 - Published by Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory\nhttp://perspectivesinmedicine.cshlp.org/\nDownloaded from", page:12}}, {_id:2941, properties:{chunk_index:0, id:"Cold Spring Harb Perspect Med-2025-Westenberger-a041774.pdf::p13::0::c13ca296", embedding:[0.03784576, 0.08053599, -0.14205685, -0.016408194, 0.0064330897, 0.012147715, 0.03214964, 0.022775345, 0.02641948, -0.03503592, -0.010775982, 0.008014119, 0.075643994, 0.017734325, -0.01323935, -0.05354615, -0.03963803, -0.019506223, 0.020330694, 0.031002691, -0.065799594, -0.02861629, -0.01340398, -0.035704028, 0.0650479, 0.0640677, -0.051901355, -0.006522089, 0.0014709571, -0.049952835, 0.068750806, -0.024763292, -0.008164333, -0.042797532, -0.032568324, -0.012344634, 0.049382158, 0.007599753, 0.03954265, 0.09196324, 0.054993603, 0.042221453, -0.006826092, -0.07534045, -0.008009601, 0.034553345, 0.034192804, 0.010816939, 0.0831299, -0.1149002, 0.05814084, 0.0051378105, 0.04297612, -0.010446851, 0.08806775, 0.010946983, -0.03723015, 0.030303108, 0.012149384, -0.056095775, 0.07164621, 0.073869795, -0.070375755, 0.019823633, 0.06029723, -0.049517494, -0.022845993, 0.005737044, 0.043473687, -0.05313383, 0.042258013, 0.0037182474, 0.045370437, 0.04791321, 0.0063225743, -0.02241335, 0.038354054, 0.011257568, -0.024806105, 0.021477347, 0.030126117, -7.8222423E-4, 0.026254036, 0.035589427, 0.03767126, 0.0041941726, -0.004346926, 0.0011729726, -0.034540754, 0.077570856, 0.05835776, 0.03373887, -0.0051599904, 0.013205071, -0.052849196, 0.019604642, -0.001832729, 0.012819636, -0.060051624, 0.00951352, -0.03427208, -0.020078138, -0.004747402, 0.01272256, -0.0014766898, 0.05743109