morphological changes in\nthe lungs of nonhuman primates (Fuji et al.\n2015). These changes have been reversible after\ndrug withdrawal and were not associated with\ncompromised pulmonary function preclinically\n(Baptista et al. 2020). Furthermore, no safety\nconcerns were raised in the ﬁrst early studies in\nhumans (Table 3), and rare loss-of-function/\nloss-of-protein variants have not yet been asso-\nciated with a pulmonary phenotype (Whifﬁn\net al. 2020).\nA. Westenberger et al.\n14\nCite this article as Cold Spring Harb Perspect Med 2025;15:a041774\nwww.perspectivesinmedicine.org\nPress \n on November 10, 2025 - Published by Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory\nhttp://perspectivesinmedicine.cshlp.org/\nDownloaded from", page:14}}, {_id:2947, properties:{chunk_index:0, id:"Cold Spring Harb Perspect Med-2025-Westenberger-a041774.pdf::p15::0::479f83a6", embedding:[0.010427855, 0.0655844, -0.17303945, -0.02551155, 0.0334101, -0.049725886, 0.06809827, 0.0077077467, 0.0010507467, -0.010710585, 0.011829751, 0.049507737, 0.064335234, -0.0075918837, 0.045783058, -0.039657887, 0.017383778, -0.04539218, -0.047056273, 0.028081564, -0.076383226, -0.02709905, -0.033760186, -0.043605935, 0.009618261, 0.07218066, -0.014427275, 0.031802457, 0.008717142, 0.02030296, 0.11678478, -0.04576969, -0.0031046376, -0.04439654, -0.003976311, -0.018451516, 0.04225751, 0.044012353, -0.01818253, -0.02254347, 0.027349047, -0.0042283526, 0.059048135, -0.07489304, -0.03672285, 0.03741147, 0.052683696, 0.06006035, 0.052637693, -0.114710264, 0.033095427, -0.023392806, 0.021115726, -0.017288934, 0.08645244, 0.00564327, -0.08359958, -0.021282777, -0.01253325, -0.043620095, 0.06263066, 0.053272486, -0.07587436, 0.02776754, 0.07282726, -0.053138644, -0.034874123, 0.06913736, 0.0047875913, -0.049465973, 0.024608932, -0.035701975, 0.03604442, 0.029313017, 0.012177422, -0.022675324, 0.0064010355, -0.0023201986, -0.025967268, 0.015678896, -0.009216613, 0.03065581, 0.081240036, -0.009714732, 0.11494991, -0.0054